Confidence Intervals and t-tests

Use the t-test function to find the confidence intervals and perform t-tests filter is subsetting by rows

## 
##  One Sample t-test
## 
## data:  ivee_lobsters
## t = 245.23, df = 2302, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true mean is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  72.99130 74.16806
## sample estimates:
## mean of x 
##  73.57968

Two sample t-test: Is there a significant difference in mean lobster lengths between Naples Reef and Mohwak Reef?

## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  napl_sample and mohk_sample
## t = 19.849, df = 1850.8, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  10.19806 12.43436
## sample estimates:
## mean of x mean of y 
##  78.18454  66.86833

Mean lobster size differ significantly between Mohawk and Naples reefs (t{r mohk_napl_ttest$parameter} = 19.849)
